{{Infobox cycling race report | name =Men's under-23 time trial | image =Jersey_rainbow chrono.svg | image_caption = [[Rainbow jersey]] | image_size =150 | series = [[2010 UCI Road World Championships]] | race_no = | series_no = | date = September 29, 2010 | stages = 1 | distance = 31.6 | unit = km | time = 42' 50.29" | speed = 44.259 | type = medals | first = [[Taylor Phinney]] | first_nat = USA | first_natvar = | first_team = United States | second = [[Luke Durbridge]] | second_nat = AUS | second_natvar = | second_team = Australia | third = [[Marcel Kittel]] | third_nat = GER | third_natvar = | third_team = Germany | previous = [[2009 UCI Road World Championships – Men's under-23 time trial|2009]] | next = [[2011 UCI Road World Championships – Men's under-23 time trial|2011]] }} {{2010 UCI Road World Championships}} The '''Men's under-23 time trial''' of the [[2010 UCI Road World Championships]] cycling event took place on 29 September in [[Melbourne]], [[Australia]].
[[Taylor Phinney]] took the United States' first gold medal in the event, since [[Danny Pate]] won in [[2001 UCI Road World Championships|Lisbon in 2001]], denying [[Australia]]'s [[Luke Durbridge]] by 1.9 seconds, who had been on top for the majority of the event, while [[Marcel Kittel]] of [[Germany]] took bronze.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/othersports/cycling/8031701/UCI-Road-World-Championships-Taylor-Phinney-wins-mens-under-23-time-trial-title.html|title=Taylor Phinney wins men's under-23 time trial title|work=[[The Daily Telegraph]]|publisher=Telegraph Media Group|date=29 September 2010|accessdate=29 September 2010}}</ref>
==Route== The race covered 31.6&nbsp;km.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.melbourne2010.com.au/default.aspx?s=u23-time-trial-flash|title=Men's under-23 time trial course|work=melbourne2010|publisher=melbourne2010.com|accessdate=7 September 2010}}</ref>
