{{Motorsport venue |Name = Albany-Saratoga Speedway |Nicknames = "The Great Race Place" |Time = GMT-5 |Location = [[Malta, New York]] |Coordinates = {{coord|42.9885|-73.7821|type:landmark_region:US-NY|display=inline,title}} |Image = File:Albany-Saratoga Speedway.jpg |Image_caption = |Capacity = |Owner = Howard Commander |Operator = Lyle DeVore |Broke_ground = |Opened = 1965 |Closed = |Construction_cost= |Architect = |Former_names = |Events = |Layout1 = Oval |Surface = Dirt |Length_km = 0.56 |Length_mi = 0.36 |Miles_first = |Turns = 4 |Banking = }}
'''Albany-Saratoga Speedway''' is an 0.36-mile dirt oval on [[U.S. Route 9 in New York|U.S. Route 9]] in [[Malta, New York]]. The track features racing on Friday nights, with five different weekly racing divisions, including DIRTcar Modifieds, DIRTcar Sportsman, Pro Stocks and Street Stocks and also Four cylinder racers.
The Speedway first opened in 1965. From 1977 It was owned by the family of C. J. Richards, a founder of the [[Champlain Valley Racing Association]]. In 2011 it was put up for sale. After a period of uncertainty as to whether it would continue to be used for racing, it was purchased by the owners of [[Lebanon Valley Speedway]] in [[New Lebanon, New York|West Lebanon, New York]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Family puts Speedway up for sale for $6 million|url=http://blog.timesunion.com/malta/family-puts-speedway-up-for-sale-for-6-million/1232/|accessdate=Jan 12, 2015|work=Daily Gazette|date=August 29, 2011}}</ref>. The speedway hosts to such divisions as Modifieds, Pro Stocks, 4 cylinders and STR's.
