{{infobox country at games | NOC = BIZ | NOCname = [[Belize Olympic and Commonwealth Games Association]] | games = Summer Olympics | year = 1976 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = [[Montreal]] | competitors = 4 | sports = 2 | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 0 | bronze = 0 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }}
'''[[Belize]]''' competed at the '''[[1976 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Montreal|Montreal, Quebec]], Canada. Previously, the nation had competed as [[British Honduras]]. Four competitors, all men, took part in four events in two sports.<ref>[https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/countries/BIZ/summer/1976/ Belize at the 1976 Montréal Summer Games]. Sports Reference. Retrieved 29 July 2015.</ref>
