The '''Gambia Football Federation''' ('''GFF'''), formerly known as the '''Gambia Football Association''', is the governing body of [[Football (soccer)|football]] in [[Gambia]]. It was founded in 1952, and affiliated to [[FIFA]] in 1968 and to [[Confederation of African Football|CAF]] in 1966. It organizes the national football league and the [[Gambia national football team|national team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2111801/Gambias-government-defies-FIFA-decision-dissolve-Football-Association.html |title=Gambia's government defies FIFA on decision to dissolve Football Association &#124; Mail Online |publisher=Dailymail.co.uk |date=2012-03-07 |accessdate=2013-12-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://thepoint.gm/africa/gambia/article/gambia-football-federation-manifesto |title=Gambia Football Federation – Manifesto - The Point Newspaper, Banjul, The Gambia |publisher=Thepoint.gm |date=2013-07-23 |accessdate=2013-12-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymaverick.co.za/article/2013-09-30-football-in-gambia-big-dreams-from-mustapha-kebbeh/#.UqJOBNJdXp5 |title=Football in Gambia: Big dreams from Mustapha Kebbeh |publisher=Daily Maverick |date=2013-09-30 |accessdate=2013-12-06}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/17241917 |title=BBC Sport - Gambian FA dissolved by Sports Ministry |publisher=Bbc.co.uk |date=2012-03-02 |accessdate=2013-12-06}}</ref>

