{{Infobox football biography |name = Kristian Javier |image = |caption = |fullname = |birth_date = {{birth date and age|1996|04|06}} |birth_place = [[Atlanta]], [[Georgia (U.S. state)|Georgia]], United States |height = {{height|m=1.78}} |currentclub = |clubnumber = |position = [[Midfielder]] |youthyears1 = {{0|0000}}–2013 |youthclubs1 = [[Brussels American School|Brussels]] |collegeyears1 = 2014–2015 |college1 = [[LaGrange College|LaGrange Panthers]] |collegecaps1 = 27 |collegegoals1 = 5 |years1 = 2016 |clubs1 = [[Peachtree City MOBA]] |caps1 = 1 |goals1 = 0 |nationalyears1 = |nationalteam1 = [[United States men's national under-18 soccer team|United States U18]] |nationalcaps1 = |nationalgoals1 = |nationalyears2 = |nationalteam2 = [[United States men's national under-20 soccer team|United States U20]] |nationalcaps2 = |nationalgoals2 = |nationalyears3 = 2016– |nationalteam3 = [[British Virgin Islands national football team|British Virgin Islands]] |nationalcaps3 = 2 |nationalgoals3 = 0 |club-update = 18:04, 7 June 2017 (UTC) |nationalteam-update = 18:04, 7 June 2017 (UTC) }}
'''Kristian Javier''' (born April 6, 1996) is an American born, [[British Virgin Islands]] [[association footballer|soccer]] player who last played for the [[Peachtree City MOBA]]{{expand acronym|date=August 2017}} in the [[United States]].
==College and club career== Javier played soccer for Brussels at the DODDS{{expand acronym|date=August 2017}} European Championships, where he was named boys' soccer athlete of the year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.stripes.com/sports/javier-s-style-made-him-a-most-dangerous-finisher-1.223474#.WTg2-OvyuUk |title=Javier's style made him a most dangerous finisher |date=1 June 2013 |accessdate=7 June 2017 |work=Stars & Stripes}}</ref> He then moved back to America to play soccer at the LaGrange College for two seasons before leaving for [[Premier Development League]] side Peachtree City MOBA,{{expand acronym|date=August 2017}} where he played one game in the [[2016 PDL season|2016 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.lagrangepanthers.com/sports/msoc/2015-16/bios/javier_kristian_7ux8?view=bio |title=Profile |accessdate=7 June 2017 |work=LaGrange Athletics}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mobasoccer.com/roster_players/13085789?mirror_id=3165105&subseason=278141 |title=Profile |accessdate=7 June 2017 |work=MOBA Soccer Academy}}</ref>
==International career== Javier made his senior international debut in a 3–0 away loss to [[Martinique national football team|Martinique]] in [[2017 Caribbean Cup qualification|qualification]] for the [[2017 Caribbean Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.concacaf.com/category/caribbean-cup-men/game-detail/266635 |title=Martinique 3-0 British Virgin Islands |date=24 March 2016 |accessdate=7 June 2017 |work=CONCACAF}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://bvinews.com/new/bvi-upbeat-about-next-match-beaten-3-0-in-martinique/ |title=BVI upbeat about next match, beaten 3-0 in Martinique |date=24 March 2016 |accessdate=7 June 2017 |work=BVI News}}</ref>
