{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2017}} {{Use Indian English|date=March 2017}} {{Infobox stadium | name = Mahakal Institute of Technology Ground | nickname = MIT Ground | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image = | caption = | fullname = Mahakal Institute of Technology Ground | former names = | location = [[Ujjain]], [[Madhya Pradesh]] | coordinates = | broke_ground = 2005 | built = | opened = 2005 | renovated = 2013 | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = [[Mahakal Institute of Technology]] | operator = [[Mahakal Institute of Technology]] | surface = | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 5,000 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = | embedded = | website = [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/11114.html cricketarchive] | publictransit = }} '''Mahakal Institute of Technology Ground''' or '''MIT Ground''' is a multi-purpose stadium in [[Ujjain]], [[Madhya Pradesh]]. The ground is mainly used for organizing matches of football, cricket and other sports.<ref> [http://www.mitujjain.ac.in/facilities/Sports.html Facilities]</ref> The ground has floodlights so that the stadium can host day-night matches. It was made considering all norms of [[Board of Control for Cricket in India|BCCI]] so that [[Ranji Trophy]] matches can be played.<ref> [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/11114_misc.html Other matches]</ref>The stadium was established in 2013 when they hosted a match of MM Jagdale Under-15 Inter Divisional Tournament between Ujjain Under-15s and Bhopal Under-15s.<ref> [https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/597/597919.html Scorecard]</ref>
