{{Infobox stadium | name = Sauðárkróksvöllur | nickname = | logo_image = | logo_caption = | image =Sauðárkróksvöllur.jpg | caption = | fullname = | former_names = | location = [[Sauðárkrókur]], [[Iceland]] | coordinates = {{coord|65.745122|-19.645743|type:landmark|display=inline, title}} | broke_ground = | built = | opened = 2004 | renovated = | expanded = | closed = | demolished = | owner = | operator = | surface = Grass | scoreboard = | cost = | architect = | project_manager = | structural engineer = | services engineer = | general_contractor = | main_contractors = | capacity = 2,500 | suites = | record_attendance = | dimensions = | acreage = | volume = | tenants = | embedded = | website = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }} '''Sauðárkróksvöllur''' is a football stadium in [[Sauðárkrókur]], [[Iceland]].
Sauðárkróksvöllur has a standing spectator capacity of about 2,500, but no permanent seating.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldfootball.org/ground.php/country/ISL/ground/2000000407|title=Sauðárkróksvöllur|publisher=World Football.org|accessdate=25 March 2012}}</ref> The open-air stadium opened in 2004, and has a grass surface.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://int.soccerway.com/venues/iceland/saudharkroksvollur/ |work=Soccerway |title=SAUÐÁRKRÓKSVÖLLUR |accessdate=2012-03-25}}</ref> It was built with a combination of public and private funding for the Icelandic Games held in the summer of 2004.<ref name=tindastoll1309/> The stadium was also used for the 2004 and 2009 youth games, the 2006 and 2007 Icelandic Athletic championships and various other large or small events. Sauðárkróksvöllur is used by the local sports club, [[UMF Tindastóll]], which helps maintain the pitch with the aid of volunteers.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tindastoll.is/index.php?pid=1331&cid=9770 |title=Sauðárkróksvöllur vinsælasti frjálsíþróttavöllurinn |work=UNGMENNAFÉLAG TINDASTÓLL |accessdate=2012-03-25}}</ref>
==References== {{Reflist |refs= <ref name=tindastoll1309>{{cite web |url=http://www.tindastoll.is/index.php?pid=1309 |title=Íþróttasvæði Tindastóls: Sauðárkróksvöllur |work=UNGMENNAFÉLAG TINDASTÓLL |accessdate=2012-03-25}}</ref> }}
