| capacity            = 
| tenants             = 
}}
'''Stadion Broodstraat''' was an [[Association football]] or soccer venue located in [[Antwerp]], [[Belgium]]. The venue hosted the [[Royal Antwerp FC]] from 1908 to 1923. It served as the main venue for the [[Football at the 1920 Summer Olympics|football]] tournament at the [[1920 Summer Olympics]].

